<HEAD>Three Children Die In House Fire</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BIRMINGHAM, England (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A woman who left her burning home to
call the fire department returned to find the blaze had killed her
three children.
   Laura McClaren, 32, who rushed to a neighbor's to call for help,
found that the front door of her home had slammed and locked when
she left.
   When fire officials arrived and broke down the door Monday
night, they found Dominique McClaren, 3, and her brother Alec, 7,
unconscious in a bathroom. Both died soon after they were carried
out of the house.
   Their 6-year-old brother Simon was found dead in another room of
the row house in the city's Edgbaston district.
   Mrs. McClaren was hospitalized with head, back and hand injuries.
