<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Spain-Miro,0137</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Thieves Steal Six Paintings By Miro</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BARCELONA, Spain (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Thieves broke into a museum today and
stole six works by Spanish surrealist painter Joan Miro.
   Officials of the Fundacion Miro museum in Barcelona said the
stolen works included oils, gouaches and pastels. ``The value of
the works is impossible to calculate,'' they said in a statement.
   The officials said the museum's night guard notified police
before dawn when he heard the sound of breaking glass.
   The officials believed two people were involved. The thieves
escaped before police arrived.
   The Barcelona-born Miro, who died in December 1983 at age 90,
formed part of an extraordinary generation of Spanish artists that
included Pablo Picasso and Salvador Dali. Miro was known worldwide
for his brilliantly colored surrealist paintings and huge
sculptures.
</TEXT>
