<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Britain-Eels,0114</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Englisham Gulps 2,000 Eels In 20 Seconds</HEAD>
<DATELINE>FRAMPTON ON SEVERN, England (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 26-year-old Englishman
gulped 2,000 fried baby eels in 20.5 seconds to win the World Elver
Eating Championship for the sixth straight year.
   Bartender Mark Ryder of Gloucester in western England on Monday
ate about one pound of the gray, wormlike baby eels known as elvers
to retain his title.
   The championship is awarded to the contestant who swallows the
most eels in the least amount of time.
   The Guinness Book of Records awards the world record to Peter
Dowdeswell who in 1978 ate an uncounted number of elvers weighing
one pound in 13.7 seconds.
