<HEAD>URGENT</HEAD>
<HEAD>American Photographer Sentenced For Drug Trafficking</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BARCELONA, Spain (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An American who says he was duped into
carrying cocaine into Spain was sentenced to six years and a day in
prison for drug trafficking, a spokesman for the U.S. Consulate in
Barcelona said today.
   Peter Cecere, the consulate spokesman, said Conan Owen was
convicted of smuggling 4.13 pounds of cocaine into Barcelona's El
Prat Airport on March 13, 1987 in a false-bottomed suitcase.
   Owen, a 23-year-old freelance photographer from Annandale, Va.,
stood trial March 26 after spending more than a year in pre-trial
detention at Barcelona's Modelo Prison.
   During the one-day trial, Judge Jose Presencia Rubio refused to
admit evidence defense lawyers said would clear Owen. A
three-member tribunal heard the case.
