<HEAD>Uganda Rustlers Kill 13 People in Raids</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KAMPALA, Uganda (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Rustlers armed with machine guns killed
13 people in cattle raids, it was reported Tuesday.
   Officials blamed the weekend raids in eastern Uganda on the
Karamojong, a tribe known for cattle rustling.
   Eight people were shot and killed in one raid on a village,
according to the government newspaper New Vision.
   In another attack, rustlers killed three people and stole cattle
and household goods, New Vision reported.
   In a third raid lasting four hours, rustlers stormed three
villages near Mbale 170 miles east of the capital of Kampala. They
stole 1,000 cattle and shot to death two people, including a
soldier, said regional government spokesman James Aleko.
