<HEAD>Nine People, Including King's Relatives, Detained in Swaziland</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MBABANE, Swaziland (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Nine people, including six princes
related to King Mswati III, have been detained without charge,
police said Tuesday.
   A South African news agency linked the detentions to last
month's convictions of 10 prominent Swazis for treason and other
political crimes.
   The latest detainees were held under an act allowing detentions
of up to 60 days without charge, said deputy police commissioner
Mnguni Simelaba. He gave no reason for the detentions.
   The South African Press Association quoted unidentified sources
as saying the detentions resulted from evidence at last month's
closed trial of the 10 Swazis, including Prince Bhekimpi, the
former prime minister.
   He was among seven defendants given 15-year prison terms for
plotting against the queen of this southern African monarchy
between 1982 and 1986.
