<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Starvation Sentence,0166</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Father Gets 60 Year-Sentence For Starvation Death Of Infant
Daughter</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HOUSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man described as retarded has been sentenced to
60 years in prison for allowing his 23-day-old daughter to starve.
   The jury which earlier found Oscar Fred Grothe, 36, guilty of
murdering his daughter, Heidi, set the sentence Monday.
   Grothe's wife, Rebecca, also faces murder charges.
   Harris County Assistant District Attorney Jim Buchanan said the
child deliberately was not fed and not given medical attention. The
couple's 2-year-old boy is healthy and shows the Grothes know how
to care for a child, Buchanan said.
   Grothe's attorney, Linda Cryer, was not allowed to present
testimony about her client's history, including his time in a state
school for the mentally retarded. She said Grothe had an I.Q. of 68.
   Ms. Cryer contended the death could have been due to the lack of
a thymus gland and an inability to retain salt. She planned to
appeal the verdict.
</TEXT>
