<HEAD>Ship Explosion Injures At Least Eight</HEAD>
<NOTE>EDS: LEADS with three grafs to UPDATE with ANSA now saying seven,
sted eight, workers injured. Pickup 3rd pvs, `ANSA reported...'</NOTE>
<DATELINE>VADO LIGURE, Italy (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An explosion in a hold of the cargo
ship Michele Damato severely burned seven workers and touched off a
fire today, the Italian news agency ANSA said.
   The agency said there were no injures among the dozens of other
people aboard the ship at the time of the blast in this port city
about 30 miles west of Genoa.
   Initial reports said eight people had been severely burned, but
ANSA later said only seven were injured.
   ANSA reported officials said they believe the blast was
triggered by gas fumes that seeped into the hold where welders were
working.
   Firefighters extinguished the flames that threatened to spread
to other parts of the vessel moored at the port's coal unloading
terminal, the agency said.
