<HEAD>Five Die In Hotel Fire In Blackpool</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BLACKPOOL, England (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A fire on Tuesday swept through a
hotel believed to have been used as a government shelter for
unemployed families, killing five people and injuring 17,
authorities said.
   The fire at the Leber Mount Hotel at this popular resort
apparently began on the ground floor of the four-story building,
said Fire Superintendent Richard Taylor, The cause was not known,
he said.
   The hotel had been divided into self-contained apartments,
according to a spokeswoman for the Lancashire Constabulary, the
regional police force.
   It was not known how many people were in the building at the
time.
   ``The whole scene was absolutely chaotic. There must have been
about 10 children inside the building. The people who live there
often leave their kids unattended,'' said Elizabeth Atkins, who
worked in a hairdresser's shop in the hotel.
</TEXT>
