<DOCNO> AP880405-0150 </DOCNO>
<FILEID>AP-NR-04-05-88 1540EDT</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>r i AM-BRF--Ghana     04-05 0135</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Ghana,0142</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Three Cabinet Members Lose Jobs in Ghana</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ACCRA, Ghana (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Three cabinet members in this West African
nation have been replaced in a shake-up, an official communique
said Tuesday.
   The statement, read on national radio, said secretaries for
mobilization and social welfare, works and housing, and health were
dismissed.
   The communique gave no reason for the changes, and it did not
say if the secretaries would be moved to others jobs.
   The country's leader, Flight Lt. Jerry Rawlings, has been
cracking down on official corruption. Authorities fired 33 police
officers a week ago and 19 others two weeks earlier, accusing them
of drug trafficking, armed robbery, and accepting bribes.
   In other changes announced Tuesday, several secretaries in the
cabinet, known as the Provisional National Defense Council, were
moved to other posts.
</TEXT>
