   Republican State Chairman Robert S.
Poliner said Tuesday that Vice President George Bush should pick
Elizabeth H. Dole to become his running mate. Poliner called Mrs.
Dole ``a class act.''
   ``If it were possible to make whatever compromises are necessary
or personal amends between the Doles and the Bushes, I think Mrs.
Dole would be an outstanding choice for vice president,'' Poliner
told reporters.
