<1ST_LINE>u p AM-Wis-DukakisWins     04-05 0039</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Wis-Dukakis Wins,30</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>BULLETIN</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MILWAUKEE (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Michael Dukakis won the Wisconsin primary
Tuesday night, quelling Jesse Jackson's momentum in the Democratic
presidential race and taking the upper hand in the see-saw struggle
for the party's 1988 nomination.
</TEXT>
