<2ND_LINE>BC-Honda-Recall,0120</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Honda to Recall 158,000 Prelude Cars</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Honda Motor Co. of Japan has notified the Transport
Ministry that it will recall 158,000 Prelude cars because of a
defective oil pressure hose in the power steering, a ministry
official said.
   The official, who spoke Tuesday on condition of anonymity, said
the Preludes to be recalled were produced between March 19, 1987
and March 31, 1988.
   Of the vehicles to be recalled, 92,497 cars were exported,
including 66,239 to the United States, 10,311 to Canada, 3,023 to
Britain and the rest to nine other countries including West Germany.
   If the hoses are not replaced the cars might leak oil, the
official said.
</TEXT>
