<2ND_LINE>BC-Britain-Fraud,0117</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Government Forms ``Serious Fraud Office''</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Serious Fraud Office, the government's new
weapon against big-time fraud, is to take over the investigation
and prosecutions in the Guinness PLC scandal, the office announced
Tuesday.
   The Guinness case previously was being investigated by
Department of Trade and Industry investigators and by Scotland
Yard's fraud squad.
   Six men, including the brewer's former chairman, have been
charged for their part in a scheme to support the company's stock
price during a takeover.
   The office, which launches operations on Wednesday, brings
together the expertise of top lawyers, accountants and police
officers borrowed from Scotland Yard's and other police
department's fraud squads.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
