<1ST_LINE>u f PM-ContinentalFares     04-05 0173</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Continental Fares,0180</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Continental Cuts Selected Fares</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DENVER (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Continental Airlines announced today a ``spring
sale'' on some tickets for travel between April 18 and June 15,
with no one-way fare greater than $99 for travel anywhere in the
mainland United States.
   The cuts of as much as 36 percent apply only to ``MaxSaver''
discount fares, the airline's cheapest fares which carry
restrictions. Tickets must be purchased in the next nine days.
   One-way sale fares to Honolulu will be $149 from Denver, Los
Angeles and San Francisco, and $199 from Newark, N.J., Cleveland,
Chicago and Houston.
   Tickets must be bought between April 6 and April 14 and some
restrictions apply.
   ``With our recent realignment of unrestricted fares, we've made
a commitment to keep prices affordable for the discretionary
traveler,'' said Doug Birdsall, the airline's senior vice president
of marketing and planning. ``The $99 transcontinental fare is a
fare the consumer knows, understands and responds to en masse,'' he
said.
   The fares are good for travel between noon Monday and noon
Thursday.
</TEXT>
