   Losers outnumbered gainers by about 10 to 9 in the overall tally
of New York Stock Exchange-listed issues, with 726 down, 669 up and
501 unchanged.
   Volume on the Big Board came to 95.25 million shares at
midafternoon.
   The Dow pierced the 2,000 mark at midmorning but then met with
considerable resistance. Traders said the downturn mirrored a
similar move southward in the bond market.
   ``The intraday sentiment on interest rates can move this market
as much as 10 or 15 points,'' said Peter Vandenberg, vice president
of trading at Shearson Lehman Hutton Inc.
   Market watchers were reluctant to draw firm conclusions because
trading volume was very light. ``The volume is not such that this
is a dramatic move in the market,'' Vandenberg said.
   Some speculated that big institutional investors were not
willing to commit themselves to equities and instead remained on
the sidelines.
   ``The internal market is not showing much enthusiasm,'' said
Ronald F. Daino, a technical analyst at Smith Barney, Harris, Upham
& Co.
