internal market is not showing much enthusiasm.''
   Market watchers were reluctant to draw firm conclusions because
trading volume remained very light.
   Some speculated that big institutional investors were not
willing to commit themselves to equities and instead remained on
the sidelines.
   ``This is one of those low-conviction markets where traders
dominate the arena'' and are influenced by ``intraday stimuli,''
said Michael Metz, a market strategist at Oppenheimer & Co.
   Despite a firming dollar and stabilizing bond prices, Metz said
it will take ``some passage of time'' for these improved
fundamentals to trigger investment interest.
   Much of the excitement centered on Woolworth, a component of the
Dow average, which remains on the most-active list for a second
consecutive day. But after rising as much as 4 earlier in the
session, Woolworth was up 2[ to 56\ at late afternoon.
