<2ND_LINE>PM-Wall Street Closing,0203</2ND_LINE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The stock market finished higher today after
seesawing in directionless trading that was marked by low volume
and caution among market participants.
   The Dow Jones industrial average rose about 20 points in an
early technical rally, then dipped into negative territory before
rising again. Analysts noted that traders were quick to cash in on
the initial upswing.
   Market watchers were reluctant to draw conclusions because
trading volume remained light.
   Despite a firming dollar and stabilizing bond prices, there was
``a lack of strong fundamentals to provide clear direction to
sustain a move in either direction,'' said Hugh Johnson, a senior
vice president at First Albany Corp.
   Analysts said traders were the main players in the market, with
individual and institutional investors remaining on the sidelines
while awaiting clearer signals on the direction of the economy.
   ``This is one of those low-conviction markets where traders
dominate the arena'' and are influenced by ``intraday stimuli,''
said Michael Metz, a market strategist at Oppenheimer & Co.
   Investors are groping for ``more direction in terms of (Federal
Reserve) policy and the economic indicators,'' Johnson said.
</TEXT>
