<1ST_LINE>r f AM-AutoRecalls     04-05 0109</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Auto Recalls,0113</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Honda Recalls Some Preludes For Power Steering Hoses</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   American Honda Motor Co. Inc. said Tuesday it
will voluntarily recall about 66,000 1988 Prelude S and Si
automobiles for replacement of power steering hoses.
   The hose can develop a slight leak under prolonged vibration at
engine temperatures, causing smoke if the fluid contacts the hot
exhaust manifold cover and possibly fire if it contacts the
manifold itself, Honda said in a written statement.
   The company said it had no reports of incidents involving such
leaks. Owners of affected vehicles will be notified and improved
hose assemblies will be installed free, the company said.
</TEXT>
